1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:02,070
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,140 --> 00:00:03,840
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:05,280 --> 00:00:06,480
Hello, this is Yang Dong Ik.

4
00:00:07,910 --> 00:00:10,250
I'm sorry, who? Gu In Ok?

5
00:00:13,350 --> 00:00:16,020
Yes, Gu In Ok is my mother. Why?

6
00:00:17,990 --> 00:00:19,190
What did you just say?

7
00:00:19,490 --> 00:00:20,560
My mother...

8
00:00:21,990 --> 00:00:23,260
What did you say happened to her?

9
00:00:29,470 --> 00:00:30,570
Hello?

10
00:00:31,170 --> 00:00:32,670
What do you mean
my mother disappeared?

11
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:37,280
My mother disappeared 30 years ago.
What prank is this?

12
00:00:37,580 --> 00:00:41,110
Who are you? Hello?

13
00:00:42,350 --> 00:00:43,450
What the heck was that?

14
00:00:44,050 --> 00:00:45,050
Hey.

15
00:00:45,850 --> 00:00:48,020
- What is it?
- I have no idea.

16
00:00:48,420 --> 00:00:49,950
I think someone saw the poster
up in Seongdam...

17
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:51,890
and decided to make a prank call.

18
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:54,490
(Onjeong Village Hall)

19
00:01:05,570 --> 00:01:08,940
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

20
00:01:10,310 --> 00:01:11,680
How's Dae Han?

21
00:01:12,310 --> 00:01:13,810
They slammed the door in his face?

22
00:01:14,580 --> 00:01:16,280
I wish that was all.

23
00:01:16,980 --> 00:01:19,880
I think they even grabbed him
by the collar.

24
00:01:22,290 --> 00:01:26,360
Dr. Yang must be absolutely furious.
Goodness.

25
00:01:26,590 --> 00:01:28,860
Why did he have to go today
of all days?

26
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:31,160
Today?

27
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:33,900
Oh my.

28
00:01:34,430 --> 00:01:36,500
- Today is...
- That's right.

29
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:38,940
Today marks 30 years...

30
00:01:38,940 --> 00:01:41,470
since your father
and In Ok disappeared.

31
00:01:57,420 --> 00:02:00,290
This fruit is in terrible shape.
It's all bruised up.

32
00:02:00,790 --> 00:02:03,800
Tell me about it.
It looks just like a broken heart.

33
00:02:04,730 --> 00:02:06,530
Every single one is
bruised and battered.

34
00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:09,370
Must you get so emotional
about fruit?

35
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,170
I am not.

36
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,670
Uncle hasn't come out yet, has he?

37
00:02:14,370 --> 00:02:15,370
No.

38
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:18,810
I really should've stopped him
when he asked for his suit.

39
00:02:19,110 --> 00:02:21,450
No, it would be worse
if he didn't try anything...

40
00:02:21,510 --> 00:02:23,250
and just gave up.

41
00:02:24,050 --> 00:02:26,250
At least if he faces it
head-on like this,

42
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:28,220
he won't have any regrets.

43
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:33,390
But Mom, is it okay
to just leave Uncle like that?

44
00:02:34,290 --> 00:02:36,690
It's better to face the pain
than to run from it.

45
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,800
Expressing how you feel
is what helps you heal.

46
00:02:47,070 --> 00:02:48,170
I'll be right back.

47
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:52,110
She's been crying constantly.

48
00:02:53,310 --> 00:02:54,310
Constantly?

49
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,980
Mom, do you know something?

50
00:02:59,450 --> 00:03:00,890
What is there that I don't know?

51
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,690
- They broke up.
- I know that, too.

52
00:03:05,260 --> 00:03:06,420
She'll get over it, right?

53
00:03:08,430 --> 00:03:11,400
Why on earth are we so tangled up
with that family?

54
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:13,700
I'm telling you,
we really should have moved.

55
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:16,170
By the way,

56
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:18,570
has that girl been quiet lately?

57
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:22,410
- Who?
- Dong Ik's daughter that likes you.

58
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:24,710
She even called me and said
she was your girlfriend.

59
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,910
She's not like that anymore.
She doesn't like me anymore.

60
00:03:35,620 --> 00:03:36,650
Dong Suk,

61
00:03:37,420 --> 00:03:40,360
my reason for living,
my everything! Dong Suk and I,

62
00:03:40,790 --> 00:03:42,430
we'll be together
no matter what anyone says!

63
00:03:42,990 --> 00:03:47,700
Dong Suk, Ji Hu, and I,
we deserve to be happy! Dong Suk,

64
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:49,630
I love you!

65
00:03:50,470 --> 00:03:53,610
Oh my gosh, what was that?
She's insane.

66
00:03:53,670 --> 00:03:57,340
- I love that. It's so moving.
- Moving? Hardly.

67
00:03:58,210 --> 00:04:00,040
I'm telling you,
I almost cried myself.

68
00:04:00,650 --> 00:04:02,980
So? So what happened then?

69
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:06,250
What do you think?
Grandfather was all, "Get out now!"

70
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:09,990
Yelling, and then Dad grabbed
Woo Jae's uncle by the collar,

71
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:13,290
yelling, "You bastard!
How dare you see my daughter?"

72
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:15,730
It was a total madhouse.

73
00:04:16,930 --> 00:04:20,600
Goodness, Dong Suk should be
dating someone suitable.

74
00:04:20,770 --> 00:04:22,700
- Honestly.
- I know, right?

75
00:04:23,170 --> 00:04:25,300
It's like some cruel twist of fate.

76
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:28,370
Is your aunt okay?

77
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:31,040
No, she looks completely miserable.

78
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:33,710
So what if it's hard?
They have to break up.

79
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:36,150
It's just not going to happen.
There's absolutely no way.

80
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:41,120
- Where are you going?
- I think I should head home.

81
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:44,360
I told you to stop worrying about
all that stuff at home for now.

82
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:47,190
How can I not worry about my family
when something so serious happened?

83
00:04:47,590 --> 00:04:49,590
If you're going to be like this,
what's the point of being apart?

84
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:52,600
Now that you've left,
you need to play hard to get.

85
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:03,880
I agree with her.

86
00:05:05,010 --> 00:05:06,010
Good.

87
00:05:13,890 --> 00:05:16,390
You're right. I have to be strong.

88
00:05:17,690 --> 00:05:19,020
I'll listen to you girls.

89
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:26,700
How on earth did it get
to this point between them?

90
00:05:27,700 --> 00:05:31,300
I guess they bonded while comforting
each other over their shared pain.

91
00:05:31,370 --> 00:05:33,100
Even if she doesn't know any better,

92
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:34,870
of all families, why them?

93
00:05:36,740 --> 00:05:39,010
So it's an absolute no
from you, right?

94
00:05:41,980 --> 00:05:43,310
How can you even ask that?

95
00:05:45,050 --> 00:05:48,090
It seems you're more hurt by this
than I realized.

96
00:05:49,190 --> 00:05:50,320
No matter how much time passes...

97
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:54,030
some things can never be forgotten.

98
00:05:55,860 --> 00:05:58,030
I'm sure the pharmacist will be
completely against it too.

99
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,810
What am I even doing?
This is driving me crazy.

100
00:06:21,450 --> 00:06:24,060
- Park Jun Hyeok.
- Get out here now!

101
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:26,160
What? Where to?

102
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:28,060
Where are you?

103
00:06:28,660 --> 00:06:29,790
I'm at Onjeong!

104
00:06:31,530 --> 00:06:32,900
A resignation letter?

105
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:36,900
Why? Why are you resigning?

106
00:06:37,270 --> 00:06:41,040
Hey, what did Ceviel offer you?
Are they paying more than Taehan?

107
00:06:41,210 --> 00:06:44,380
What offer?
I haven't even met with Ceviel yet.

108
00:06:44,510 --> 00:06:47,410
What? Then why are you quitting?

109
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:51,380
Don't tell me you're quitting
to stop Director Yang from leaving.

110
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:54,890
Director Yang...

111
00:06:55,650 --> 00:06:59,260
He has a lot going on
with his family right now.

112
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:01,990
So?

113
00:07:02,290 --> 00:07:06,100
I can't let him quit
and leave because of me.

114
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:11,000
So you resigned without even
having another job lined up?

115
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,770
Come to think of it...

116
00:07:14,270 --> 00:07:15,310
I...

117
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:17,740
realized he's always been
the one giving.

118
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:23,880
He was always first to reach out
and go out of his way for me.

119
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:29,550
With his help, I got Mom's approval
and achieved my dream.

120
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:32,760
But...

121
00:07:33,990 --> 00:07:36,760
I've never done anything for him.

122
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:42,930
Knowing full well it wouldn't work,
I only hurt him by asking him out.

123
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:47,870
And now...

124
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:50,740
For the sake of
his family's happiness,

125
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:54,110
a man who finally came home
after being away for 16 years...

126
00:07:55,210 --> 00:07:57,880
to make him leave again,
to make him lonely again...

127
00:08:01,020 --> 00:08:02,220
Letting that happen...

128
00:08:02,850 --> 00:08:04,460
is just too selfish, isn't it?

129
00:08:09,330 --> 00:08:10,660
Hey, look...

130
00:08:10,930 --> 00:08:13,260
Isn't there a way
for you both to stay?

131
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:21,140
About me dating Director Yang...

132
00:08:21,810 --> 00:08:23,540
My mom found out.

133
00:08:25,340 --> 00:08:28,150
And when I said I'd resign,

134
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:30,410
she actually agreed to it.

135
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:33,520
I guess that means
she wants us to break up.

136
00:08:36,190 --> 00:08:38,190
Hey, I'm asking you a favor.

137
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:41,560
Please take good care of
Director Yang, okay?

138
00:08:56,940 --> 00:08:59,080
(Gong Ju Ah)

139
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,850
Hey, how's Mother doing?

140
00:09:08,220 --> 00:09:09,790
You coward.

141
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:11,160
What?

142
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:15,290
You're gutless, selfish,
and a classic avoider.

143
00:09:16,060 --> 00:09:17,060
Knock it off.

144
00:09:17,130 --> 00:09:20,500
Okay, fine. That was middle school.
But how old are you now?

145
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:23,630
You just run away when it's tough?
You're the eldest son!

146
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:26,700
How can you just bail
when our family is a complete mess?

147
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:28,670
I might not go.

148
00:09:29,470 --> 00:09:30,470
Really?

149
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:34,510
Why? Did Ju Ah say something?

150
00:09:35,350 --> 00:09:38,050
What are you talking about?
Why would you bring her up now?

151
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:42,190
Because I asked Ju Ah
to talk you out of leaving.

152
00:09:42,620 --> 00:09:43,620
What?

153
00:09:44,420 --> 00:09:47,260
So that's why she suddenly quit.

154
00:09:47,790 --> 00:09:49,590
Seriously, why would you do that?

155
00:09:50,130 --> 00:09:53,330
No way. She quit her job?

156
00:09:54,070 --> 00:09:56,800
She'd go that far to make you stay?

157
00:09:57,130 --> 00:10:00,640
She's so much better than you.
She's better off without you.

158
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:14,720
You're home earlier than I expected.

159
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:17,790
Wasn't today your last shoot?
Did you skip the wrap party?

160
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:21,490
Come on, how could I go to a party
when you're sick?

161
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:26,030
Still, you should've had a drink
with the crew to unwind.

162
00:10:26,130 --> 00:10:27,300
No, it's fine.

163
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:30,130
I didn't want to waste my breath
on that jerk, Bucket.

164
00:10:30,940 --> 00:10:33,470
Did Bucket say anything?

165
00:10:33,570 --> 00:10:37,640
He did! He said if he sees Dae Han,
he'll kill him, so...

166
00:10:37,710 --> 00:10:39,080
I just told him I'd kill him first.

167
00:10:39,140 --> 00:10:43,110
That's ridiculous.
It's not like his crush was one-way.

168
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:47,690
I know, right?
Anyway, how's Dae Han doing?

169
00:10:48,920 --> 00:10:50,620
Same as usual.

170
00:10:52,060 --> 00:10:53,960
Hey, Seong Mi.

171
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:58,130
About that text message
from your father...

172
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:01,430
The one telling me
not to look for him again?

173
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:03,670
Yes, that one.

174
00:11:04,340 --> 00:11:06,540
You don't think someone
was just messing with us?

175
00:11:06,940 --> 00:11:11,140
- A prank?
- Yes, they saw our flyers and...

176
00:11:11,410 --> 00:11:12,840
It's possible, right?

177
00:11:13,710 --> 00:11:14,710
Are you disappointed?

178
00:11:14,980 --> 00:11:19,650
No, no. It's just someone
prank-called Bucket today.

179
00:11:19,950 --> 00:11:22,190
So I looked
at the text message again,

180
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,120
and no matter how I look at it,

181
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:26,990
it just doesn't sound like Father.

182
00:11:28,090 --> 00:11:30,900
If you want to look for him,
let's just do it quietly.

183
00:11:31,530 --> 00:11:34,300
If we find Mother and Father,

184
00:11:35,170 --> 00:11:37,130
they've decided to get a divorce.

185
00:11:37,870 --> 00:11:39,000
A divorce?

186
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:40,700
Yes.

187
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:53,380
Grandfather, what is all this?

188
00:11:53,950 --> 00:11:56,290
Grandfather, is this because
Mom isn't here?

189
00:11:56,450 --> 00:11:58,390
Leave me be.
Today, I'll do as I please.

190
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:01,690
Yes, just let him drink
as much as he wants.

191
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:05,000
He's already upset today,
and then Dong Suk had to pile on...

192
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:07,500
What's so special about today?

193
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:13,970
Come on, what is it?
Why won't anyone tell me?

194
00:12:14,270 --> 00:12:18,040
It's the 30th anniversary
of Grandma leaving.

195
00:12:24,550 --> 00:12:26,020
Go on and drink, Grandfather.
I mean...

196
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:28,350
Even Mom couldn't say no
to you today.

197
00:12:38,030 --> 00:12:39,030
Father.

198
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,500
Do you still resent Mother
that much?

199
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:44,270
Resent her?

200
00:12:45,070 --> 00:12:47,510
Do you think I resent their mother?

201
00:12:48,540 --> 00:12:51,540
- Pardon?
- I have regrets.

202
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:53,310
It's all my fault.

203
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:56,380
How on earth is that your fault,
Father?

204
00:12:57,450 --> 00:13:00,220
I remember that day vividly.

205
00:13:00,450 --> 00:13:03,750
Even so, I shouldn't have hit her.

206
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:06,760
You hit her?

207
00:13:08,030 --> 00:13:09,090
You must have been pushed to it.

208
00:13:10,190 --> 00:13:12,300
I don't think you were in the wrong,
Father.

209
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:14,000
You, be quiet and go...

210
00:13:15,270 --> 00:13:16,900
worry about your own family.

211
00:13:18,470 --> 00:13:19,470
Eun Bin.

212
00:13:19,940 --> 00:13:22,370
- Yes?
- Go make me some ramyeon.

213
00:13:23,340 --> 00:13:24,440
The spiciest you can find.

214
00:13:25,740 --> 00:13:29,350
Grandfather, that's enough now.
Mother will worry.

215
00:13:29,710 --> 00:13:32,220
Grandfather, I'm telling Mom on you!

216
00:13:36,850 --> 00:13:40,220
You're right.
I should stop for Se Ri's sake.

217
00:13:41,290 --> 00:13:42,490
Just one more glass.

218
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,200
Gosh...

219
00:13:58,310 --> 00:13:59,310
Uncle.

220
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:05,720
How's your mom doing?

221
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:07,720
She's sleeping.

222
00:14:09,250 --> 00:14:11,020
I'll tell her to have some
when she wakes up.

223
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:14,630
You knew, didn't you?

224
00:14:16,430 --> 00:14:20,230
- Yes.
- You should've stopped her!

225
00:14:21,270 --> 00:14:22,330
Come on, Uncle.

226
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:25,370
Can you really stop love?

227
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:33,680
Hey.

228
00:14:34,450 --> 00:14:36,450
Why are you here alone?
Is Uncle not coming?

229
00:14:36,610 --> 00:14:39,580
No, that's not it.
He's not in his room.

230
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:41,950
What? You're kidding. At this hour?

231
00:15:03,940 --> 00:15:05,340
Thanks for coming out to meet me.

232
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,280
What you saw earlier...

233
00:15:10,410 --> 00:15:13,020
I was worried
that'd be your last memory of me.

234
00:15:15,950 --> 00:15:17,960
I'm sorry for showing up
without discussing it with you.

235
00:15:20,090 --> 00:15:21,090
Don't be.

236
00:15:22,590 --> 00:15:23,590
But...

237
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,230
If I hadn't done that,

238
00:15:27,930 --> 00:15:29,330
I would've regretted it forever.

239
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:32,040
You're right.

240
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:34,140
You would have.

241
00:15:35,740 --> 00:15:36,840
You did the right thing.

242
00:15:46,850 --> 00:15:48,020
This is my last gift to you.

243
00:15:51,860 --> 00:15:53,190
(Our Bucket List)

244
00:15:53,260 --> 00:15:55,260
Our bucket list.

245
00:15:56,230 --> 00:15:59,730
I listed everything I wanted to do
with you and Ji Hu.

246
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:02,570
Even when I'm gone,

247
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:05,170
make sure you two do all of them.

248
00:16:05,870 --> 00:16:08,010
(5. Eat a meal together
as a family of three)

249
00:16:08,810 --> 00:16:10,970
Giving me homework
even as we say goodbye.

250
00:16:12,180 --> 00:16:13,180
Dong Suk.

251
00:16:14,910 --> 00:16:16,010
Don't you ever...

252
00:16:16,610 --> 00:16:18,450
give up on the simple joys of life.

253
00:16:19,420 --> 00:16:21,420
And don't you ever forget
how beautiful, precious,

254
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,890
and treasured you are.

255
00:16:26,420 --> 00:16:27,420
I won't.

256
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:30,890
You deserve to be loved.

257
00:16:33,230 --> 00:16:34,400
So do you.

258
00:16:37,670 --> 00:16:38,870
You know...

259
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,270
In this life,

260
00:16:41,810 --> 00:16:44,040
I have no regrets,
all thanks to you.

261
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:47,480
I...

262
00:16:50,810 --> 00:16:52,620
The love you've given me,

263
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:59,860
I'll cherish it
for the rest of my life.

264
00:17:02,790 --> 00:17:03,930
If...

265
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:09,500
Even if I could turn back time,

266
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,070
I'd fall in love with you
all over again.

267
00:17:18,340 --> 00:17:19,340
Me too.

268
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:02,750
Ji Hu, what are you doing out here?

269
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:05,720
Gosh, Mom,
I'm so disappointed in you.

270
00:18:07,790 --> 00:18:08,790
Why?

271
00:18:09,690 --> 00:18:11,200
You should have just run away
with Mr. Gong.

272
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:13,560
Why did you come back?

273
00:18:45,260 --> 00:18:46,900
(Ji Hu)

274
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:48,070
Mr. Gong.

275
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:53,170
Thank you for loving and taking care
of my mom and me all this time.

276
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:58,740
I'll protect my mom from now on,
so please don't you worry.

277
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:03,810
In my next life,
I hope I'm born as your son.

278
00:19:41,020 --> 00:19:42,020
Dae Han.

279
00:19:42,550 --> 00:19:43,550
Mom.

280
00:19:45,620 --> 00:19:46,890
Hey, why are you out here?

281
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:50,730
It looked like
it was suddenly going to rain.

282
00:19:54,460 --> 00:19:55,730
Afraid I might have run off?

283
00:19:59,300 --> 00:20:00,770
It would've been better if you had.

284
00:20:05,380 --> 00:20:06,440
Goodness, Mom.

285
00:20:07,710 --> 00:20:12,020
You know, Mom.
Dad left us 30 years ago today.

286
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:14,350
If...

287
00:20:15,420 --> 00:20:17,220
Dong Suk and I had run away today,

288
00:20:19,890 --> 00:20:21,390
that would've been
front-page news, right?

289
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:26,760
I guess so.

290
00:20:29,730 --> 00:20:30,830
Don't worry.

291
00:20:31,970 --> 00:20:32,970
That won't happen.

292
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:35,840
Let's go, Mom.

293
00:20:39,710 --> 00:20:40,840
Have you been out here in the cold?

294
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:21,420
With what bastard...

295
00:21:23,620 --> 00:21:28,030
What were you doing and where
to come before your kids like this?

296
00:21:29,230 --> 00:21:31,700
And you call yourself a mother?

297
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:36,200
Honey.

298
00:21:37,530 --> 00:21:39,740
- Dad.
- Get out!

299
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:43,270
Get out!

300
00:21:43,810 --> 00:21:47,040
How could you?
How could you do this to me?

301
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:50,080
Get out!

302
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:53,780
Get out of my house!

303
00:22:07,060 --> 00:22:10,200
Grandfather, are you all right?
Can I get you some water?

304
00:22:11,370 --> 00:22:13,740
If you're not feeling up to it,
you can eat later.

305
00:22:13,970 --> 00:22:17,110
You think you'd feel fine
after eating that much before bed?

306
00:22:18,210 --> 00:22:19,610
I'm so sorry, Father.

307
00:22:20,580 --> 00:22:21,650
It's because of me.

308
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:25,120
You even had a drink,
and you never do.

309
00:22:28,690 --> 00:22:32,860
- Eun Bin, you saw Mom yesterday?
- Yes.

310
00:22:33,290 --> 00:22:36,660
She didn't have any message for me?

311
00:22:37,390 --> 00:22:38,660
Yes, there was something.

312
00:22:42,230 --> 00:22:45,400
Mr. Kim, who remodeled our clinic,
passed away.

313
00:22:45,470 --> 00:22:48,000
She said to be sure to send a wreath
and condolence money.

314
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:50,570
Is that it?

315
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:56,150
There's more.
The accountant, the herb supplier.

316
00:22:56,210 --> 00:22:57,610
She said to take care of it all
by tomorrow.

317
00:22:58,550 --> 00:22:59,620
That's it?

318
00:23:00,580 --> 00:23:02,520
What else were you expecting?

319
00:23:05,290 --> 00:23:06,990
You should just go see her.

320
00:23:07,820 --> 00:23:09,630
I tried to go,

321
00:23:10,790 --> 00:23:12,660
but I couldn't work up the nerve.

322
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:17,170
Hyun Bin isn't going to Argentina.

323
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:21,840
Yang Eun Bin.

324
00:23:22,240 --> 00:23:25,780
What? You're going to go then?
Someone gave up their spot for you.

325
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:26,980
Will you shut up?

326
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:35,650
Ju Ah, you're changing jobs?

327
00:23:35,850 --> 00:23:39,660
- Yes, taking that scouted offer.
- Why the sudden change?

328
00:23:40,390 --> 00:23:45,160
The pay and conditions are better,
and, well, it's closer to home.

329
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:49,470
That's right.
Sometimes you need a change to grow.

330
00:23:50,670 --> 00:23:51,670
Yes.

331
00:23:52,540 --> 00:23:56,340
Ju Ah, if you're free,
please buy your mom a healthy meal?

332
00:23:56,910 --> 00:23:59,840
- What are you in the mood for?
- How about I treat you?

333
00:24:00,310 --> 00:24:03,280
That's okay. It's a ladies' day out.
We're going for a drive.

334
00:24:03,750 --> 00:24:06,520
- What do you think, Mother?
- Sure.

335
00:24:06,980 --> 00:24:09,590
Let's do it.
I've been cooped up, so it's nice.

336
00:24:10,890 --> 00:24:15,530
- You two can handle lunch, right?
- What?

337
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:20,530
Yes.

338
00:24:21,230 --> 00:24:26,200
I'm sorry for the trouble I caused.
Ju Ah, Woo Jae, I'm so sorry, okay?

339
00:24:27,270 --> 00:24:29,770
Dong Suk and I had a clean break,
so please don't worry.

340
00:24:32,540 --> 00:24:35,880
What about your plan to leave here
and start your own practice?

341
00:24:36,010 --> 00:24:37,550
I'm still planning on doing that.

342
00:24:38,150 --> 00:24:40,620
It would be too hard
to keep meeting at work, you know?

343
00:24:44,350 --> 00:24:45,590
This is good.

344
00:24:46,690 --> 00:24:49,130
You should try this. It's so good.
The bean sprouts are delicious.

345
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:54,930
(9. Creating our own
neighborhood walking trail)

346
00:24:55,130 --> 00:24:56,700
(13. Exploring a night market
and trying all the food)

347
00:24:56,770 --> 00:24:58,130
(14. Making a packed lunch together)

348
00:25:11,380 --> 00:25:12,380
Se Ri.

349
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:14,580
Do you like living on your own?

350
00:25:15,050 --> 00:25:16,690
Dong Suk, are you okay?

351
00:25:17,220 --> 00:25:19,790
I was so worried about you
I couldn't sleep a wink.

352
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:23,230
That Eun Bin...

353
00:25:24,130 --> 00:25:26,860
Why did she have to go and tell you?

354
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:30,800
Dong Suk, you can't do that.
You know that, right?

355
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:34,540
Father will never allow you
to get your own place.

356
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:36,840
I know.

357
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:40,880
I'm sorry to be the one to say it.

358
00:25:41,710 --> 00:25:43,250
No, it's okay. You're right.

359
00:25:46,620 --> 00:25:50,990
We broke up, so don't worry.
Sorry to make you worry.

360
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:56,290
Are you enjoying the time
with your daughter?

361
00:25:57,260 --> 00:26:01,230
It's nice, but I'm dying to go home.

362
00:26:01,970 --> 00:26:05,970
Be patient. Why did we separate
if you were coming back so soon?

363
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:09,870
I'll head over there.
Can you meet me for a bit?

364
00:26:10,170 --> 00:26:13,810
Let's get some good food
and some fresh air. I'm on my way.

365
00:26:13,940 --> 00:26:15,780
Go where?
Where do you think you're going?

366
00:26:28,730 --> 00:26:31,460
Mom, did she really step outside
just to take that call?

367
00:26:32,060 --> 00:26:36,430
She was all hiding and going,
"I'll be there soon." I swear.

368
00:26:36,670 --> 00:26:40,840
I wasn't on the phone with your dad.
It was your aunt.

369
00:26:41,270 --> 00:26:45,480
We're separated, not divorced.
I still have to care for the family.

370
00:26:45,540 --> 00:26:48,080
I told you to give him
the cold shoulder.

371
00:26:48,180 --> 00:26:52,220
Dad will never change
if you keep doing it all for him.

372
00:26:52,380 --> 00:26:54,950
What do you mean he's not changing?
Compared to before, your dad...

373
00:26:55,020 --> 00:26:57,190
There you go again, taking his side.

374
00:26:57,720 --> 00:27:01,460
Mom, what's wrong with you?
Why are you the only one in love?

375
00:27:04,730 --> 00:27:06,300
What's with you?
Why are you laughing?

376
00:27:07,430 --> 00:27:11,230
You're not exactly one to talk.

377
00:27:11,740 --> 00:27:12,740
She's right.

378
00:27:13,640 --> 00:27:15,910
But Mom, I do agree with her.

379
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:19,880
A relationship where one person
does all the work isn't healthy.

380
00:27:20,210 --> 00:27:23,450
See? Even Min Seo
who goes to Johns Hopkins agrees.

381
00:27:23,450 --> 00:27:24,610
Okay, fine! I get it!

382
00:27:25,020 --> 00:27:26,220
I'll listen to you two.

383
00:27:27,420 --> 00:27:28,590
Then I'll take...

384
00:27:30,020 --> 00:27:31,020
Let go!

385
00:27:31,450 --> 00:27:33,290
- Confiscated.
- Hey!

386
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:38,260
Today, we'll forget everything
and just have fun together. Got it?

387
00:27:39,300 --> 00:27:40,300
Answer.

388
00:27:40,900 --> 00:27:41,900
Answer me!

389
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:48,200
What?

390
00:27:48,870 --> 00:27:49,910
Min Seo, here you go.

391
00:27:51,340 --> 00:27:54,680
I'm on a diet.
You eat it, Mom. Here!

392
00:27:56,180 --> 00:27:57,310
Tteokbokki.

393
00:27:57,910 --> 00:27:58,920
Mom...

394
00:27:59,880 --> 00:28:00,980
That scared me!

395
00:28:03,250 --> 00:28:04,290
This kid...

396
00:28:04,790 --> 00:28:07,960
- She really gave me a fright.
- How do I look?

397
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:09,860
Gosh, Eun Bin.

398
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:14,900
- So pretty.
- I'm going to layer it with this.

399
00:28:15,100 --> 00:28:16,100
Good.

400
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:23,110
(Look at the lens
and press the shutter button.)

401
00:28:23,540 --> 00:28:26,510
"Flower pose." One, two, three!

402
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:29,450
- Mom, make a heart!
- A heart?

403
00:28:43,560 --> 00:28:45,960
I could have made
the baeksuk myself.

404
00:28:46,430 --> 00:28:49,930
But I was craving it,
and I searched all day for the best.

405
00:28:50,100 --> 00:28:53,540
I worry about you coming this far
when you're not well.

406
00:28:53,900 --> 00:28:55,610
It's nice to get out for a drive,
isn't it?

407
00:28:56,510 --> 00:28:59,140
It's so good to get some fresh air
for a change.

408
00:28:59,540 --> 00:29:00,540
Isn't that right, Mother?

409
00:29:00,980 --> 00:29:02,280
Yes, it's lovely.

410
00:29:02,580 --> 00:29:05,580
I'll take you out more often
during your treatments, Mom.

411
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:07,280
I'd love that.

412
00:29:09,290 --> 00:29:11,690
I just wish I didn't have to
go through chemotherapy.

413
00:29:14,690 --> 00:29:15,730
Mother.

414
00:29:16,030 --> 00:29:20,760
Did you know many women get divorced
right after their mastectomy?

415
00:29:21,100 --> 00:29:24,900
- What? No, who on earth would...
- That's unbelievable.

416
00:29:25,340 --> 00:29:28,940
Now that my Gong Jeong Han
has turned over a new leaf,

417
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:30,340
how wonderful is that?

418
00:29:30,970 --> 00:29:33,240
He's probably making up
with Dae Han now, right?

419
00:29:33,780 --> 00:29:36,650
That's why we're giving them space.
I'm sure they'll work it out.

420
00:29:37,450 --> 00:29:40,480
They're not fighting again,
are they?

421
00:29:47,020 --> 00:29:48,020
Jeong Han.

422
00:29:48,530 --> 00:29:49,530
What is it?

423
00:29:52,300 --> 00:29:53,400
I...

424
00:29:54,130 --> 00:29:55,300
I need to apologize.

425
00:29:56,330 --> 00:29:57,330
For what?

426
00:29:58,170 --> 00:30:02,740
I'm sorry for what I said,
for lording it over you.

427
00:30:03,570 --> 00:30:04,740
For crying out loud...

428
00:30:06,810 --> 00:30:08,550
I know everything. All right?

429
00:30:09,310 --> 00:30:12,480
I know how good you were
to my wife and the kids.

430
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:17,950
How you've always given in to me
and sacrificed for our family.

431
00:30:18,020 --> 00:30:19,420
I know all that.

432
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:24,230
But I was just so caught off guard
and flustered that...

433
00:30:24,290 --> 00:30:26,660
I was just running my mouth.

434
00:30:28,930 --> 00:30:30,500
I'm sorry for lashing out
at you, too.

435
00:30:31,100 --> 00:30:32,270
You...

436
00:30:32,540 --> 00:30:36,140
I know this is the first time
you've wanted something so much,

437
00:30:37,310 --> 00:30:40,540
but it just had to be the one thing
that's out of the question.

438
00:30:41,610 --> 00:30:43,680
I'm sorry I can't help you with it.

439
00:30:46,020 --> 00:30:47,080
It's not your fault.

440
00:30:47,480 --> 00:30:50,090
I knew it was impossible.
I was just being childish.

441
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:51,920
Hey, Dae Han.

442
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:57,130
Let's just forget about Father
and focus on Mom from now on, okay?

443
00:30:58,630 --> 00:31:00,300
But hey, I'm really...

444
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:04,300
- I'm not leaving because I'm mad.
- Yes, I know.

445
00:31:04,770 --> 00:31:07,600
I'll also look for a hospital
with a good offer for you.

446
00:31:08,570 --> 00:31:09,770
Hey, and...

447
00:31:11,170 --> 00:31:12,180
Here.

448
00:31:13,510 --> 00:31:14,510
What's this?

449
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:16,050
It's money.

450
00:31:16,710 --> 00:31:19,480
Come on.
You don't have money to spare.

451
00:31:19,650 --> 00:31:23,190
No, it's just some emergency cash
I've been saving. It's not much.

452
00:31:23,250 --> 00:31:24,750
It's to help you find a place.

453
00:31:24,820 --> 00:31:26,620
No, no, I can't.
What are you thinking?

454
00:31:26,690 --> 00:31:28,460
What if your wife finds out?
Hey, just put it away.

455
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:32,960
- Hey, my wife okayed it. Come on...
- She did?

456
00:31:36,500 --> 00:31:38,130
Seriously...

457
00:31:40,470 --> 00:31:41,470
I'll pay you back.

458
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:44,840
Hey, so, you...

459
00:31:45,340 --> 00:31:48,440
So what happened
between you and Dong Suk?

460
00:31:48,850 --> 00:31:49,880
Why are you asking?

461
00:31:49,950 --> 00:31:53,350
What do you mean, "why?"
Of course I'm curious!

462
00:31:53,450 --> 00:31:54,450
Come on, tell me.

463
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:57,290
I don't know. It just happened.
Why do you keep asking?

464
00:31:57,350 --> 00:32:00,690
Come on, you little punk.
Give me some details.

465
00:32:01,490 --> 00:32:02,530
Unbelievable.

466
00:32:03,890 --> 00:32:05,230
Okay, so...

467
00:32:06,130 --> 00:32:09,070
I was upset about Hui Gyeong,
so I was having a drink,

468
00:32:10,430 --> 00:32:13,900
and Dong Suk was drinking nearby.
So we ended up at the same table.

469
00:32:13,970 --> 00:32:15,670
Right, right. And then?

470
00:32:15,740 --> 00:32:20,110
I don't know if it was the alcohol,
but Dong Suk looked so beautiful.

471
00:32:20,880 --> 00:32:23,310
So? So you just went for it
and kissed her?

472
00:32:23,380 --> 00:32:25,920
Are you crazy? No, not then.

473
00:32:26,220 --> 00:32:30,520
- So when was it?
- It was, let's see...

474
00:32:30,590 --> 00:32:32,760
The day I went to file the...
the divorce papers.

475
00:32:33,190 --> 00:32:35,830
Afterwards,
the two of us just hung out.

476
00:32:35,960 --> 00:32:39,530
Played the claw machine, then ate.
By the way, Dong Suk loves shrimp.

477
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:43,400
Goodness. So that's when you just
went for it and kissed her?

478
00:32:44,200 --> 00:32:45,200
You sly dog.

479
00:32:45,600 --> 00:32:47,540
Whatever. Why are you asking?

480
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:53,540
I'm just going to the bathroom.

481
00:33:10,730 --> 00:33:12,060
Sit down for a second.

482
00:33:19,900 --> 00:33:20,900
Why?

483
00:33:21,800 --> 00:33:22,810
I lost my temper yesterday.

484
00:33:25,740 --> 00:33:26,740
I'm sorry.

485
00:33:27,410 --> 00:33:30,150
You could have just talked to him
and sent him home nicely.

486
00:33:30,580 --> 00:33:33,020
Why did you grab him by the collar?
And why throw fruit at him?

487
00:33:33,780 --> 00:33:35,350
You weren't exactly
in the right, either.

488
00:33:35,990 --> 00:33:36,990
I know.

489
00:33:37,990 --> 00:33:39,620
I knew it was impossible,

490
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:41,760
but I couldn't help being selfish.

491
00:33:42,890 --> 00:33:44,830
I know Dae Han's a good guy.

492
00:33:45,860 --> 00:33:47,300
If our situation were different,

493
00:33:47,860 --> 00:33:48,970
I would've been grateful.

494
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,100
Anyway, I'm sorry.

495
00:33:52,870 --> 00:33:54,300
How is this your fault?

496
00:33:55,540 --> 00:33:56,740
It's all Mom's fault.

497
00:33:58,780 --> 00:34:00,310
Do you want to move out with Ji Hu?

498
00:34:01,580 --> 00:34:03,580
I'll figure out a way
to get you a place.

499
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:06,950
It'll be awkward for you,
living so close to Dae Han.

500
00:34:07,150 --> 00:34:10,490
It's fine. Father gave me the store.

501
00:34:10,490 --> 00:34:11,550
You...

502
00:34:11,820 --> 00:34:13,390
If you're thinking about
getting married again,

503
00:34:13,660 --> 00:34:15,290
I can set you up on some dates.

504
00:34:17,230 --> 00:34:18,230
I'm not interested.

505
00:34:18,860 --> 00:34:19,960
I'm...

506
00:34:20,300 --> 00:34:22,300
never going to date
anyone ever again.

507
00:34:22,630 --> 00:34:23,630
Why?

508
00:34:24,330 --> 00:34:25,330
Because you got hurt?

509
00:34:25,770 --> 00:34:26,770
No.

510
00:34:27,340 --> 00:34:28,470
Because I've had my fill.

511
00:34:29,810 --> 00:34:31,270
The truth is,

512
00:34:31,670 --> 00:34:33,510
the things I've never
heard from anyone,

513
00:34:33,940 --> 00:34:36,010
the love I've never
received from anyone...

514
00:34:36,510 --> 00:34:38,110
I got everything
I ever wanted from him.

515
00:34:49,030 --> 00:34:52,260
Mom, I should be the one doing that.

516
00:34:52,300 --> 00:34:56,130
Don't worry about it. I've got it.
There you go.

517
00:34:56,700 --> 00:34:58,200
All you have to do is enjoy it.

518
00:34:58,700 --> 00:35:00,200
Thank you.

519
00:35:01,740 --> 00:35:02,740
Ju Ah.

520
00:35:03,570 --> 00:35:05,210
Why aren't you eating?

521
00:35:05,480 --> 00:35:07,310
You usually have such
a great appetite.

522
00:35:08,610 --> 00:35:11,110
What's wrong?
You don't like the baeksuk?

523
00:35:11,850 --> 00:35:14,120
No, it's just...

524
00:35:14,450 --> 00:35:17,090
Seeing the baeksuk
just reminded me of something.

525
00:35:18,390 --> 00:35:20,520
Someone? You mean Director Yang?

526
00:35:20,820 --> 00:35:21,820
Yes.

527
00:35:22,290 --> 00:35:24,260
You really enjoy teasing me,
don't you?

528
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:28,260
Keep talking about him.
It'll help you get over it.

529
00:35:29,230 --> 00:35:31,800
Just eat your food, Mother.

530
00:35:37,610 --> 00:35:40,480
Bucket's wife has been very quiet,
hasn't she?

531
00:35:40,910 --> 00:35:42,750
With all this drama going on
in both families.

532
00:35:43,950 --> 00:35:47,680
They've got more going on than
just the issue with their uncle.

533
00:35:50,820 --> 00:35:54,990
If you're going to start a story,
finish it. Don't leave us hanging.

534
00:35:57,930 --> 00:36:00,530
Sweetie, you don't have to talk
if it makes you uncomfortable.

535
00:36:00,630 --> 00:36:03,000
No, tell us. I'm curious.

536
00:36:05,070 --> 00:36:08,800
Apparently, Director Yang's mother
has a biological daughter.

537
00:36:09,670 --> 00:36:12,740
- Oh my gosh.
- Wait, really? Is that true?

538
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:15,480
Yes. She was put up for adoption
a long time ago,

539
00:36:15,550 --> 00:36:17,110
and they just recently reconnected.

540
00:36:17,980 --> 00:36:20,120
And Bucket didn't know about it?

541
00:36:20,380 --> 00:36:22,920
I don't know the details. Why?

542
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:26,690
Because if she hid that from him,
that's grounds for divorce.

543
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:30,160
At this rate, Bucket's going to get
divorced again.

544
00:36:30,590 --> 00:36:33,530
It does seem like they're in
a bit of a crisis.

545
00:36:33,700 --> 00:36:37,530
So Dae Han visited them
while their family was in turmoil.

546
00:36:38,900 --> 00:36:42,100
All right, let's not gossip
about other families.

547
00:36:42,470 --> 00:36:45,880
The secret kick to this baeksuk
is the pickled chili peppers.

548
00:36:46,080 --> 00:36:50,680
Here, try some with the peppers.
Grandma, you have some too.

549
00:36:50,780 --> 00:36:53,780
It makes it so much more delicious.
Okay, my turn.

550
00:36:56,050 --> 00:36:59,260
Dip the meat in the broth a little,

551
00:36:59,290 --> 00:37:03,060
and top it with a pickled chili.
They're the secret kick.

552
00:37:08,360 --> 00:37:11,270
She's right, Mother.
It really is delicious together.

553
00:37:12,070 --> 00:37:14,400
I'm going to get some more
pickled chili peppers.

554
00:37:20,010 --> 00:37:22,450
Did Ju Ah quit her job
because of Director Yang?

555
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:24,880
Yes.

556
00:37:26,380 --> 00:37:29,350
Director Yang was meant to quit,
but because of his family situation,

557
00:37:29,720 --> 00:37:31,490
I guess he can't go
to Argentina anymore.

558
00:37:32,860 --> 00:37:33,960
That's what it looks like.

559
00:37:37,260 --> 00:37:38,260
I see.

560
00:37:39,730 --> 00:37:43,730
He just found his family again.
I was worried he'd leave, too.

561
00:37:46,300 --> 00:37:48,070
Speaking of which, Gong Ju Ah...

562
00:37:48,370 --> 00:37:50,640
has always been one to get
whatever she sets her mind to.

563
00:37:55,380 --> 00:37:56,780
She seems to be taking it hard,
doesn't she?

564
00:37:58,110 --> 00:37:59,120
Yes.

565
00:38:00,120 --> 00:38:02,750
I guess she liked him more
than she let on.

566
00:38:17,270 --> 00:38:18,270
So,

567
00:38:18,630 --> 00:38:23,340
- Ms. Gong is quitting after all?
- Yes. I couldn't convince her.

568
00:38:24,510 --> 00:38:26,080
The nerve of them.
What do they think this company is?

569
00:38:27,740 --> 00:38:29,910
Especially when Father went so far
to help in his condition.

570
00:38:30,250 --> 00:38:31,980
Tell me about it.

571
00:38:32,680 --> 00:38:35,750
I hear Managing Director Hong
is already pulling all the strings.

572
00:38:36,020 --> 00:38:37,920
This just played right into
Director Baek's hands.

573
00:38:39,490 --> 00:38:40,490
Wait, but...

574
00:38:40,920 --> 00:38:43,360
I don't know if I should be asking,

575
00:38:43,730 --> 00:38:45,930
but what's Director Baek's deal,
anyway?

576
00:38:46,300 --> 00:38:49,300
If he wants to take over,
he has to gut the fashion division.

577
00:38:50,070 --> 00:38:52,640
Gosh, he only got that job
thanks to the Chairman.

578
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:54,270
You're so naive.

579
00:38:55,570 --> 00:38:57,710
Right. I'm that naive.

580
00:38:58,170 --> 00:38:59,480
I don't know the first thing
about any of that.

581
00:39:04,110 --> 00:39:06,850
Anyway, how's the Chairman today?

582
00:39:09,390 --> 00:39:10,720
You know how he's in and out?

583
00:39:11,250 --> 00:39:12,390
Well, today he's out.

584
00:39:13,690 --> 00:39:14,890
You must be so worried.

585
00:39:16,130 --> 00:39:17,860
If he never snaps out of it,

586
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:20,630
I'll be the first one
on the chopping block.

587
00:39:21,530 --> 00:39:22,730
I'm in real trouble.

588
00:39:23,500 --> 00:39:25,400
I don't have anyone to back me up.

589
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:27,400
Gosh, what are you going to do?

590
00:39:27,940 --> 00:39:30,540
If you need someone in your corner,
I can do that.

591
00:39:31,540 --> 00:39:32,540
As if.

592
00:39:34,680 --> 00:39:37,980
Well, if the Chairman
has a lucid moment,

593
00:39:38,450 --> 00:39:40,080
could you give him this?

594
00:39:41,220 --> 00:39:42,220
What's this?

595
00:39:42,690 --> 00:39:45,050
What did you bring?
Father was looking forward to it.

596
00:39:45,990 --> 00:39:49,230
It's Shanghai butter rice cakes
and chocolate caneles.

597
00:39:50,790 --> 00:39:52,930
- Did you get one for me?
- Of course.

598
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:55,660
- Want the butter rice cake?
- Sure.

599
00:39:56,930 --> 00:39:57,930
Ta-da!

600
00:39:58,900 --> 00:40:00,300
It's so pretty.

601
00:40:01,500 --> 00:40:03,470
- Can I have this?
- Of course.

602
00:40:06,010 --> 00:40:07,840
- This is delicious.
- You like it?

603
00:40:09,650 --> 00:40:12,350
Mom, why'd you want to stop here?
You must be tired.

604
00:40:12,410 --> 00:40:15,280
I just felt bad that we were
the only ones eating something nice.

605
00:40:15,420 --> 00:40:18,750
Okay, let's quickly grab something
for Dae Han and get going.

606
00:40:18,820 --> 00:40:20,290
- Okay.
- There.

607
00:40:20,390 --> 00:40:21,990
- Oh, my, Dr. Han!
- Hello.

608
00:40:22,060 --> 00:40:25,260
- The surgery went well, right?
- Yes, of course.

609
00:40:25,490 --> 00:40:30,230
That's such a relief.
We were all so worried about you.

610
00:40:30,300 --> 00:40:33,440
- You were?
- Of course we were.

611
00:40:34,270 --> 00:40:37,510
You're the pride of Onjeong,
Dr. Han.

612
00:40:37,870 --> 00:40:39,640
We were all praying for you.

613
00:40:40,010 --> 00:40:41,480
Thank you so much.

614
00:40:42,240 --> 00:40:44,910
I'll focus on my recovery
and get well soon.

615
00:40:45,010 --> 00:40:47,280
Of course. You have to.

616
00:40:47,780 --> 00:40:51,990
We really miss seeing you
on your show.

617
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:55,620
We'd like the salted pollack roe
and the seasoned fish cakes, please.

618
00:40:55,690 --> 00:40:57,290
The pollack roe? Here you go.

619
00:40:58,290 --> 00:40:59,300
Oh, dear.

620
00:40:59,700 --> 00:41:02,530
Mother,
I guess people haven't forgotten me.

621
00:41:03,230 --> 00:41:06,600
Of course. Did you think Dr. Han's
popularity would just vanish?

622
00:41:06,940 --> 00:41:09,710
Maybe I should offer free consults
around the neighborhood.

623
00:41:09,770 --> 00:41:13,010
Gosh, just focus on resting.
What are you talking about?

624
00:41:13,380 --> 00:41:15,040
- By the way, Mom.
- Yes?

625
00:41:15,110 --> 00:41:16,250
Here you are.

626
00:41:16,510 --> 00:41:18,550
- Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

627
00:41:18,610 --> 00:41:20,120
- Have a good one.
- You take care of yourself now.

628
00:41:21,450 --> 00:41:23,690
Let's go. What? Hey...

629
00:41:25,620 --> 00:41:26,620
Bucket.

630
00:41:27,020 --> 00:41:29,790
- Mom, come on. Why?
- Hold on.

631
00:41:34,700 --> 00:41:36,730
Hey, you. My husband...

632
00:41:37,570 --> 00:41:38,730
Did you grab him by the collar?

633
00:41:39,740 --> 00:41:41,140
He was being childish.

634
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:43,010
He had it coming.

635
00:41:45,510 --> 00:41:46,510
What about you?

636
00:41:47,380 --> 00:41:48,610
Are you feeling any better?

637
00:41:49,550 --> 00:41:50,550
Yes.

638
00:41:51,210 --> 00:41:53,150
So the surgery went well?

639
00:41:54,220 --> 00:41:55,220
Yes.

640
00:41:55,580 --> 00:41:57,650
Good.
I know you'll make a full recovery.

641
00:41:59,260 --> 00:42:00,660
I hear you have a daughter now?

642
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:01,960
What?

643
00:42:03,660 --> 00:42:04,660
Yes.

644
00:42:04,930 --> 00:42:06,500
All right, bye then.

645
00:42:07,600 --> 00:42:08,830
Wait, Seong Mi.

646
00:42:10,170 --> 00:42:11,170
What is it?

647
00:42:11,570 --> 00:42:12,640
If you have a minute,

648
00:42:13,840 --> 00:42:15,040
I could use some advice...

649
00:42:17,840 --> 00:42:18,840
Advice?

650
00:42:19,610 --> 00:42:21,210
What do you need advice about?

651
00:42:22,650 --> 00:42:24,850
You know I specialize in
family matters, right?

652
00:42:25,680 --> 00:42:26,720
Of course.

653
00:42:27,420 --> 00:42:30,290
It's impossible to book you,
and you're the best.

654
00:42:31,690 --> 00:42:33,020
I feel bad asking
since you're recovering,

655
00:42:33,690 --> 00:42:34,690
but please, help me out.

656
00:42:39,430 --> 00:42:41,800
All right.
Tell me what's on your mind.

657
00:42:43,630 --> 00:42:46,070
What seems to be the problem?

658
00:42:47,900 --> 00:42:51,270
But what I'm about to tell you,
you can't tell a single soul.

659
00:42:51,540 --> 00:42:52,880
Client confidentiality...

660
00:42:53,580 --> 00:42:56,750
is a fundamental principle,
so you don't have to worry.

661
00:42:58,910 --> 00:42:59,920
Seong Mi.

662
00:43:01,420 --> 00:43:02,480
What is love?

663
00:43:03,390 --> 00:43:04,390
What?

664
00:43:05,090 --> 00:43:06,420
We're separated.

665
00:43:08,360 --> 00:43:10,360
What? Separated?

666
00:43:15,160 --> 00:43:16,270
That's a common issue.

667
00:43:18,070 --> 00:43:22,140
Can you tell me the specific reason
why you separated?

668
00:43:25,840 --> 00:43:27,410
I thought my wife
was having an affair,

669
00:43:28,240 --> 00:43:30,550
I hired a private detective agency
to investigate, and she found out.

670
00:43:30,610 --> 00:43:33,380
A private detective agency?
What were you thinking?

671
00:43:37,020 --> 00:43:38,020
You promised. Confidentiality.

672
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,900
The approach is crucial,
especially as you've broken trust.

673
00:43:49,730 --> 00:43:52,470
Right now, anything you say
will just sound like an excuse.

674
00:43:53,100 --> 00:43:54,700
Exactly. You're absolutely right.

675
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:56,910
That's why this time,
more than ever...

676
00:44:00,240 --> 00:44:01,540
At times like this,
what's important...

677
00:44:02,040 --> 00:44:03,610
is consistent action...

678
00:44:04,210 --> 00:44:05,310
and sincerity.

679
00:44:07,580 --> 00:44:08,580
Wow, that's golden.

680
00:44:09,420 --> 00:44:10,520
Hey, can I get a piece of paper?

681
00:44:23,670 --> 00:44:24,670
I've decided...

682
00:44:25,630 --> 00:44:28,200
to divorce your father.

683
00:44:29,610 --> 00:44:30,610
A divorce?

684
00:44:32,010 --> 00:44:34,310
Seong Mi already told me.

685
00:44:36,180 --> 00:44:38,780
You've been married for so long.
Why now all of a sudden?

686
00:44:40,450 --> 00:44:43,820
I just want to take this chance
to get a clean slate,

687
00:44:44,820 --> 00:44:47,760
and let go of
all the resentment and hate.

688
00:44:48,590 --> 00:44:50,930
But we don't even know
where Father is.

689
00:44:52,130 --> 00:44:53,200
Can you still get a divorce?

690
00:44:54,100 --> 00:44:57,670
Yes, apparently there's a way,

691
00:44:57,830 --> 00:44:59,170
if we prove his whereabouts
are unknown.

692
00:44:59,400 --> 00:45:02,940
Yes, a friend of Seong Mi's
is a family lawyer.

693
00:45:04,170 --> 00:45:06,840
As a matter of fact,
I already have a meeting scheduled.

694
00:45:07,840 --> 00:45:08,840
Right.

695
00:45:20,960 --> 00:45:23,060
Mother.

696
00:45:25,530 --> 00:45:26,530
What are you doing?

697
00:45:31,630 --> 00:45:35,640
Just sorting through the letters
I wrote your father over the years.

698
00:45:37,840 --> 00:45:39,240
That's a good idea.

699
00:45:42,110 --> 00:45:44,380
This is all just baggage, I suppose?

700
00:45:45,550 --> 00:45:46,550
Exactly.

701
00:45:47,220 --> 00:45:49,280
Physically decluttering
can also bring...

702
00:45:49,720 --> 00:45:52,350
a sense of psychological release.

703
00:45:56,060 --> 00:45:58,630
I wrote so many.

704
00:46:09,940 --> 00:46:12,440
(3H Acupressure Beds)

705
00:46:13,410 --> 00:46:14,410
Oh my, what's this?

706
00:46:15,580 --> 00:46:17,410
(3H Acupressure Beds)

707
00:46:18,450 --> 00:46:21,650
Oh my, Mom.
Looks like someone cleaned in here.

708
00:46:22,580 --> 00:46:24,250
You're right.

709
00:46:24,990 --> 00:46:26,590
I wonder who did this.

710
00:46:28,120 --> 00:46:31,130
Who else could it be?
Probably whoever left the flowers.

711
00:46:36,470 --> 00:46:39,970
I worried your throat might get sore
from dealing with customers,

712
00:46:40,570 --> 00:46:43,210
so I bought you some throat syrup
and a scarf.

713
00:46:44,210 --> 00:46:45,440
That's so sweet.

714
00:46:47,180 --> 00:46:48,910
Gosh, seriously.

715
00:46:49,310 --> 00:46:51,810
(Free Flu Shots)

716
00:46:57,050 --> 00:46:58,650
(Cleaning the Mattress Store,
Giving a Gift)

717
00:47:03,260 --> 00:47:06,500
You mean Ms. Gong's quitting?
That makes no sense.

718
00:47:07,300 --> 00:47:10,000
What? Did I tell her to quit?
Why are you getting mad at me?

719
00:47:10,670 --> 00:47:14,340
You should've stopped her, Mr. Park.
You two are best friends.

720
00:47:14,600 --> 00:47:17,540
I did try to stop her.
But you know what Ms. Gong is like.

721
00:47:17,610 --> 00:47:19,440
Once she makes a decision,
she never changes it.

722
00:47:19,610 --> 00:47:22,480
Don't tell me she's going to Ceviel.

723
00:47:23,010 --> 00:47:26,220
Yes. It looks like she's leaving
after the styling class.

724
00:47:26,820 --> 00:47:31,550
But I thought she wasn't leaving.
Did she get some incredible offer?

725
00:47:32,620 --> 00:47:33,760
That could be it.

726
00:47:34,220 --> 00:47:37,490
FG's future looks bleak
since all our bids are blocked.

727
00:47:38,130 --> 00:47:40,630
Maybe jumping ship now
is the right call.

728
00:47:40,900 --> 00:47:43,930
Hey, everyone, let's stop
with the wild speculation, okay?

729
00:47:44,400 --> 00:47:49,100
But if she goes to Ceviel,
she'll be our competitor.

730
00:47:52,110 --> 00:47:53,110
Man.

731
00:47:55,310 --> 00:47:56,310
So, what's everyone saying?

732
00:47:57,180 --> 00:47:59,350
What do you think?
They're losing their minds.

733
00:47:59,750 --> 00:48:01,450
I'll talk to them again
and smooth things over.

734
00:48:02,720 --> 00:48:03,720
Ms. Gong.

735
00:48:05,550 --> 00:48:06,560
Oh, hello.

736
00:48:07,820 --> 00:48:08,820
Just a moment.

737
00:48:14,930 --> 00:48:17,970
Did you resign because of Eun Bin?
Is that why?

738
00:48:18,270 --> 00:48:20,640
No. I made the decision before that.

739
00:48:21,640 --> 00:48:24,510
I'll sort out
my family matters quickly...

740
00:48:24,810 --> 00:48:25,970
and leave as scheduled.

741
00:48:26,580 --> 00:48:27,580
Excuse me?

742
00:48:27,910 --> 00:48:31,350
- I already handed in my notice.
- Fine, that's your decision.

743
00:48:31,680 --> 00:48:33,080
But I'm sticking to mine.

744
00:48:33,480 --> 00:48:34,820
I've already submitted
my resignation.

745
00:48:34,920 --> 00:48:37,350
It hasn't been processed yet.
So withdraw it.

746
00:48:37,420 --> 00:48:39,760
Director Yang, are you really going
to be like this?

747
00:48:39,820 --> 00:48:43,390
You're the one being unreasonable.
If I let you quit and I stay,

748
00:48:43,460 --> 00:48:44,460
what does that make me?

749
00:48:44,660 --> 00:48:48,030
Look, it's not like
I'm quitting design altogether.

750
00:48:48,100 --> 00:48:50,370
I'm just moving to a new company
to further my career.

751
00:48:50,430 --> 00:48:53,600
Then build your career here.
At Taehan.

752
00:48:53,700 --> 00:48:56,540
Is there any reason I should
listen to you, Director Yang?

753
00:49:09,150 --> 00:49:10,920
- Thank you.
- Take good care of yourself.

754
00:49:13,520 --> 00:49:15,290
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

755
00:49:38,010 --> 00:49:39,650
What seems to be the trouble, ma'am?

756
00:49:40,450 --> 00:49:44,550
- Pardon me?
- The doctor's office or the clinic?

757
00:49:45,390 --> 00:49:47,420
The Korean medicine clinic.

758
00:49:48,490 --> 00:49:50,430
- This way then.
- Okay.

759
00:49:51,460 --> 00:49:52,460
Bye then.

760
00:49:54,560 --> 00:49:56,930
All right, sir.
Thank you for your patience today.

761
00:49:57,370 --> 00:49:58,870
- Yes.
- Thank you.

762
00:49:58,930 --> 00:50:00,500
- All right, watch your step.
- Okay.

763
00:50:01,000 --> 00:50:02,840
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

764
00:50:02,900 --> 00:50:03,940
Welcome.
Are you here for the clinic?

765
00:50:04,810 --> 00:50:05,870
First time here?

766
00:50:06,270 --> 00:50:10,750
- Are you Dr. Yang Dong Ik?
- Yes. That's me.

767
00:50:11,050 --> 00:50:12,850
How would you like me to sign...

768
00:50:12,850 --> 00:50:14,250
No. I'm sorry.

769
00:50:14,750 --> 00:50:16,350
So, what brings you in?

770
00:50:17,520 --> 00:50:18,750
Gu In Ok...

771
00:50:20,090 --> 00:50:22,420
You're her son, right?

772
00:50:27,960 --> 00:50:31,000
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

773
00:50:31,070 --> 00:50:32,370
What gives?

774
00:50:33,070 --> 00:50:34,070
Why are you here?

775
00:50:34,400 --> 00:50:35,400
Jeong Han.

776
00:50:35,740 --> 00:50:36,740
What?

777
00:50:37,640 --> 00:50:39,370
That call you got
from the senior center...

778
00:50:40,440 --> 00:50:41,440
It wasn't a prank call.

779
00:50:42,510 --> 00:50:43,580
What? What are you talking about?

780
00:50:44,480 --> 00:50:45,480
My mom...

781
00:50:46,210 --> 00:50:47,250
I found her.

782
00:50:51,020 --> 00:50:53,490
Bucket's mother is in the hospital?

783
00:50:54,360 --> 00:50:55,460
Then what about Father?

784
00:50:55,960 --> 00:50:56,960
Is he with her?

785
00:50:59,530 --> 00:51:03,130
I don't have all the details yet.
I'll go find out and call you back.

786
00:51:03,670 --> 00:51:07,440
Listen, don't say anything
to Mom yet.

787
00:51:08,240 --> 00:51:09,240
Right.

788
00:51:15,710 --> 00:51:18,210
Hey, that person who called you.

789
00:51:18,880 --> 00:51:20,020
The one who came to see you...

790
00:51:20,750 --> 00:51:22,050
Who is she?

791
00:51:27,460 --> 00:51:30,160
How do you know my mother?

792
00:51:30,760 --> 00:51:33,400
My name is Laywoman Myeong Ryun.

793
00:51:33,960 --> 00:51:35,500
At Soun Temple,
I'm known as Laywoman Yeon Sim.

794
00:51:36,000 --> 00:51:37,730
You see...

795
00:51:38,200 --> 00:51:41,200
I work with Gu In Ok.
We make meals together there.

796
00:51:42,640 --> 00:51:45,110
My mother is living at a temple?

797
00:51:45,910 --> 00:51:48,080
Right now, she's in the hospital.

798
00:51:48,910 --> 00:51:50,980
- The hospital?
- Yes.

799
00:51:51,480 --> 00:51:55,120
She went up the mountain to pray
two days ago and never came back.

800
00:51:55,820 --> 00:51:59,350
She said it was exactly thirty years
since she left home.

801
00:51:59,820 --> 00:52:04,490
She saw her family on TV recently
and seemed very conflicted,

802
00:52:05,160 --> 00:52:07,660
so I wondered if she might have
gone back home.

803
00:52:08,260 --> 00:52:11,770
I called the TV station and got
your number, Dr. Yang.

804
00:52:12,530 --> 00:52:15,240
But why is my mother
in the hospital?

805
00:52:16,540 --> 00:52:18,870
On her way down the mountain
after praying,

806
00:52:19,810 --> 00:52:21,780
she lost her footing and fell.

807
00:52:25,880 --> 00:52:26,880
So, does that mean...

808
00:52:27,650 --> 00:52:28,820
Is it serious?

809
00:52:30,290 --> 00:52:31,290
Looks like it.

810
00:52:31,990 --> 00:52:33,590
They told me to call the family.

811
00:52:42,030 --> 00:52:47,170
(Dongwoo University Hospital)

812
00:52:47,240 --> 00:52:49,070
The information desk, over here.

813
00:52:49,370 --> 00:52:52,610
- We're here for Gu In Ok in the ER.
- Right this way.

814
00:52:55,740 --> 00:52:57,850
- This is her son.
- Are you Yang Dong Ik?

815
00:52:58,010 --> 00:53:00,020
- Yes, I am.
- This way, please.

816
00:53:00,880 --> 00:53:03,350
(Dongwoo University Hospital
Information)

817
00:53:10,190 --> 00:53:12,630
Excuse me...

818
00:53:13,560 --> 00:53:17,470
The man who was with Gu In Ok,
did he happen to come with you?

819
00:53:18,370 --> 00:53:21,000
He should have been with her
for the last thirty years.

820
00:53:21,240 --> 00:53:23,770
I only came to Soun Temple
a few years ago.

821
00:53:24,910 --> 00:53:27,210
But the Head Monk
of Soun Temple here...

822
00:53:27,410 --> 00:53:29,910
has been here since
Laywoman Yeon Sim first arrived.

823
00:53:30,250 --> 00:53:32,380
Yes. Hello.

824
00:53:33,110 --> 00:53:35,020
Who was it you were asking about?

825
00:53:35,280 --> 00:53:37,820
A man named Gong Gi Cheol.

826
00:53:38,690 --> 00:53:40,990
He would have been with Gu In Ok.

827
00:53:41,690 --> 00:53:44,960
He's my father.

828
00:54:13,820 --> 00:54:14,820
Why?

829
00:54:15,790 --> 00:54:17,060
Why are you here like this?

830
00:54:21,130 --> 00:54:23,300
Why would you reappear like this?

831
00:54:27,840 --> 00:54:28,840
Mom.

832
00:54:43,690 --> 00:54:46,720
Laywoman Yeon Sim
came to Soun Temple...

833
00:54:47,460 --> 00:54:48,820
alone.

834
00:54:50,960 --> 00:54:51,960
Excuse me?

835
00:54:52,430 --> 00:54:55,800
The moment
I first saw her that day...

836
00:54:56,400 --> 00:54:58,370
I still remember it vividly.

837
00:54:59,430 --> 00:55:01,400
There was no one with her.

838
00:55:02,240 --> 00:55:05,310
No, that can't be right.

839
00:55:10,250 --> 00:55:11,250
Alone?

840
00:55:11,750 --> 00:55:15,150
- You mean In Ok was there alone?
- Yes.

841
00:55:15,580 --> 00:55:19,050
So, did she and Father split up
and she was living alone?

842
00:55:19,450 --> 00:55:20,890
And they don't know where Father is?

843
00:55:21,560 --> 00:55:23,060
I don't know about that.

844
00:55:23,430 --> 00:55:26,830
Hey, when did they say
In Ok joined the temple?

845
00:55:27,560 --> 00:55:31,730
They said she went to the temple
the day she left home, 30 years ago.

846
00:55:32,000 --> 00:55:33,000
What?

847
00:55:34,100 --> 00:55:35,170
That's impossible.

848
00:55:36,100 --> 00:55:38,210
Mom, are you okay?

849
00:55:40,580 --> 00:55:43,310
- What in the world is going on?
- Wait a second. I...

850
00:55:44,080 --> 00:55:46,780
I can't think straight right now.
What is all this?

851
00:55:48,450 --> 00:55:49,450
The two of them...

852
00:55:50,120 --> 00:55:53,120
I don't think
they left home together.

853
00:55:54,190 --> 00:55:55,790
So you're saying
they weren't having an affair?

854
00:56:01,130 --> 00:56:02,130
Gosh.

855
00:56:05,000 --> 00:56:06,000
An affair?

856
00:56:06,870 --> 00:56:08,570
I wouldn't know about that.

857
00:56:10,140 --> 00:56:14,080
She said she was homeless
and asked to stay a while.

858
00:56:15,040 --> 00:56:17,110
And for 30 years, she quietly...

859
00:56:17,550 --> 00:56:20,850
served as the cook at Soun Temple.

860
00:56:23,990 --> 00:56:25,920
I haven't read this myself,

861
00:56:26,890 --> 00:56:29,590
but I brought it in case
it might be helpful.

862
00:56:31,090 --> 00:56:32,090
Thank you.

863
00:56:40,570 --> 00:56:42,600
(Intensive Care Unit)

864
00:56:43,370 --> 00:56:45,910
(Dongwoo University Hospital)

865
00:56:49,440 --> 00:56:53,410
Hey. How's she doing?

866
00:56:54,820 --> 00:56:57,820
We should get Father and Dong Suk
here while she's still conscious.

867
00:57:02,920 --> 00:57:04,990
Hey, Dong Ik.

868
00:57:06,430 --> 00:57:07,900
Your mother...

869
00:57:09,500 --> 00:57:12,600
Apparently,
she didn't leave with my father.

870
00:57:14,400 --> 00:57:15,940
What are you talking about?

871
00:57:17,270 --> 00:57:18,570
Your mother...

872
00:57:19,410 --> 00:57:21,010
was apparently alone the whole time.

873
00:57:21,880 --> 00:57:22,940
What are you...

874
00:57:24,310 --> 00:57:25,380
Then what about your father?

875
00:57:26,850 --> 00:57:28,150
I don't know.

876
00:57:28,650 --> 00:57:30,080
And this.

877
00:57:31,020 --> 00:57:33,560
The head monk asked me
to give this to you.

878
00:57:34,820 --> 00:57:36,990
It's a diary your mother kept...

879
00:57:37,990 --> 00:57:39,460
all these years.

880
00:57:54,880 --> 00:57:57,150
Yes, Mr. Gong.
What can I do for you?

881
00:57:57,610 --> 00:57:58,610
Hello.

882
00:57:59,250 --> 00:58:02,180
I'm calling because
I think we need to find my father.

883
00:58:03,520 --> 00:58:05,390
So you've decided to file
a missing person report?

884
00:58:06,190 --> 00:58:10,530
Yes. And could you tell me
what I'll need?

885
00:58:10,930 --> 00:58:14,200
Okay. First, I'll need a photo
and his personal information.

886
00:58:14,430 --> 00:58:16,100
Okay. And what else?

887
00:58:16,460 --> 00:58:20,570
Then I'll need his physical details,
like height, weight, moles, scars.

888
00:58:20,800 --> 00:58:23,500
You'll also need to describe
his disappearance in as much detail,

889
00:58:23,770 --> 00:58:25,610
so it would be best
if you could prepare those details.

890
00:58:26,340 --> 00:58:28,980
Yes, thank you. Okay.

891
00:58:31,880 --> 00:58:35,120
How could I have been so certain
they ran off together?

892
00:58:35,820 --> 00:58:39,020
The night before,
Father and Director Yang's mother...

893
00:58:39,090 --> 00:58:41,990
Someone saw them embracing,
remember?

894
00:58:43,890 --> 00:58:45,160
Who was that again?

895
00:58:45,530 --> 00:58:46,660
It was more than one person.

896
00:58:47,300 --> 00:58:49,260
That rumor was all over
the neighborhood.

897
00:58:50,430 --> 00:58:53,800
People said they saw them,
and they vanished on the same day,

898
00:58:54,440 --> 00:58:57,670
So I guess we've all had it wrong
for 30 years.

899
00:58:58,510 --> 00:58:59,640
Then...

900
00:59:00,380 --> 00:59:04,250
Was that
"don't look for me" text a prank?

901
00:59:04,850 --> 00:59:05,850
What?

902
00:59:06,980 --> 00:59:10,420
What if your father went off
and died somewhere?

903
00:59:10,750 --> 00:59:13,620
If he had,
we would've been notified.

904
00:59:15,920 --> 00:59:17,460
How's In Ok doing?

905
00:59:18,930 --> 00:59:20,530
She seems to be
in critical condition.

906
00:59:21,300 --> 00:59:24,270
Director Yang has called his family
to the hospital.

907
00:59:26,600 --> 00:59:27,600
Oh no.

908
00:59:28,440 --> 00:59:29,440
Let's go.

909
00:59:30,510 --> 00:59:33,780
I'm going too.
I think I need to see In Ok.

910
00:59:33,840 --> 00:59:35,310
Mom, do you want to go?

911
00:59:36,240 --> 00:59:40,280
Yes. If I was wrong...

912
00:59:42,620 --> 00:59:45,950
If I've spent 30 years
hating an innocent In Ok...

913
00:59:47,090 --> 00:59:48,360
How can I possibly face her?

914
00:59:50,120 --> 00:59:51,130
Mother...

915
00:59:54,260 --> 00:59:56,260
(Angiography Room)

916
01:00:07,910 --> 01:00:09,240
Your mother...

917
01:00:11,010 --> 01:00:15,080
She wasn't having an affair
with Gi Cheol.

918
01:00:17,290 --> 01:00:18,290
Right.

919
01:00:21,290 --> 01:00:22,360
In our neighborhood...

920
01:00:23,690 --> 01:00:25,590
She was assaulted.

921
01:00:35,100 --> 01:00:37,070
- Dad.
- Get out!

922
01:00:38,470 --> 01:00:40,680
How could you do this to me?

923
01:00:41,340 --> 01:00:43,880
Get out!

924
01:00:47,280 --> 01:00:48,480
You and I, Father...

925
01:00:50,490 --> 01:00:51,750
We had no idea.

926
01:01:04,700 --> 01:01:07,140
Mom.

927
01:01:12,570 --> 01:01:13,980
Mom.

928
01:01:16,510 --> 01:01:20,280
Mom, you should have
at least told me.

929
01:01:21,480 --> 01:01:24,290
You should have denied it.

930
01:01:25,050 --> 01:01:29,420
How could you hide away like that?
Mom, how did you live all this time?

931
01:01:30,660 --> 01:01:31,660
How...

932
01:01:32,390 --> 01:01:36,060
How could you live like that? Mom!

933
01:01:41,300 --> 01:01:44,240
(Dongwoo University Hospital)

934
01:01:44,310 --> 01:01:46,840
(Intensive Care Unit)

935
01:01:47,040 --> 01:01:49,240
Father, aren't you going in?

936
01:01:51,350 --> 01:01:53,920
Why can't you go in, Father?

937
01:01:55,180 --> 01:01:59,290
Go in! Just go in, Father!

938
01:02:06,390 --> 01:02:10,430
What do we do with Mom? Father!

939
01:02:12,300 --> 01:02:14,640
Father, what are we going to do
about Mom?

940
01:02:15,440 --> 01:02:17,510
What's going to happen to her?

941
01:03:06,890 --> 01:03:10,090
(Intensive Care Unit)

942
01:03:17,930 --> 01:03:19,430
Honey.

943
01:03:25,510 --> 01:03:26,510
I just...

944
01:03:34,820 --> 01:03:36,450
Mom...

945
01:03:41,490 --> 01:03:42,560
Mom.

946
01:03:45,030 --> 01:03:46,030
In Ok.

947
01:03:53,470 --> 01:03:54,470
I...

948
01:03:56,300 --> 01:03:57,710
was wrong.

949
01:04:08,880 --> 01:04:09,880
I'm so...

950
01:04:12,250 --> 01:04:13,520
sorry.

951
01:04:36,210 --> 01:04:37,710
Ma'am!

952
01:04:48,060 --> 01:04:51,830
Code Blue, Intensive Care Unit.

953
01:04:52,830 --> 01:04:57,060
Code Blue, Intensive Care Unit.

954
01:05:31,100 --> 01:05:33,970
(Recipe For Love)

955
01:05:36,640 --> 01:05:38,810
Find out what that bastard is up to.

956
01:05:39,070 --> 01:05:43,010
I believe there's only one way
I can be forgiven for this sin.

957
01:05:43,340 --> 01:05:47,050
Shouldn't your aunt and uncle
be able to get back together then?

958
01:05:47,920 --> 01:05:49,820
Maybe I should spread some rumors
around the neighborhood.

959
01:05:50,380 --> 01:05:52,390
We're also considering foul play.

960
01:05:52,390 --> 01:05:53,950
By any chance,
could it be that she made...

961
01:05:53,950 --> 01:05:56,820
- an enemy 30 years ago?
- Who on earth would...
